cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

The paper deals with a novel multicasting scheme in a wireless network, which involves the use of caching and stochastic geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory concepts, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The proposed scheme involves the use of delay tolerance and energy-throughput-delay tradeoff, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of massive content delivery, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of large-scale networks, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
